# CVEs in kube-linter v0.8.3's own transitive dependencies. kube-linter's
# maintainers haven't bumped these deps yet, and v0.8.3 is the latest
# release as of this writing - there's no newer version to pick up fixes
# from. kube-linter runs here as a local CLI static-analysis tool over
# manifests checked out in CI, not as a network-facing server, so the
# exploitability of these (mostly server/network-facing) CVEs is low in
# this context. Re-check on kube-linter's next release and drop whichever
# of these it resolves. Entries expire below to force that re-check.

# google.golang.org/grpc v1.75.1 (fixed 1.79.3) - gRPC-Go server authz
# bypass via malformed HTTP/2 :path; kube-linter isn't a gRPC server here.
CVE-2026-33186 exp:2026-10-07

# github.com/containerd/containerd v1.7.30 (fixed 1.7.32 / 1.7.33)
CVE-2026-46680 exp:2026-10-07
CVE-2026-53488 exp:2026-10-07

# oras.land/oras-go/v2 v2.6.0 (fixed 2.6.1), pulled in via helm.sh/helm/v3
CVE-2026-50151 exp:2026-10-07

# golang.org/x/net v0.48.0 (fixed 0.53.0 / 0.55.0)
CVE-2026-39821 exp:2026-10-07
CVE-2026-33814 exp:2026-10-07
CVE-2026-27136 exp:2026-10-07
CVE-2026-25681 exp:2026-10-07

# golang.org/x/crypto v0.46.0 (fixed 0.52.0)
CVE-2026-46597 exp:2026-10-07
CVE-2026-46595 exp:2026-10-07
CVE-2026-42508 exp:2026-10-07
CVE-2026-39835 exp:2026-10-07
CVE-2026-39832 exp:2026-10-07
CVE-2026-39831 exp:2026-10-07
CVE-2026-39830 exp:2026-10-07
CVE-2026-39829 exp:2026-10-07
CVE-2026-39828 exp:2026-10-07
